version.description:
Released in October 2010, Unicode 6.0 was the first version of the Unicode Standard to support emoji.

Some characters in prior versions of Unicode were retroactively updated to provide an emoji presentation. This release was the first to introduce new characters for the sole purpose of compatability with emojis being used in Japan.

bn:00102884a: Of, relating to, or denoting the sex which is generally characterized as the one associated with the larger gametes (for species which have two sexes and for which this distinction can be made).
Being the sex (of plant or animal) that produces fertilizable gametes (ova) from which offspring develop
Belonging to the sex with larger, fertilizable gametes.

Belonging to the sex which typically produces eggs, which in humans and most other mammals is typically the one which has XX chromosomes; belonging to the sex which has larger gametes (for species which have two sexes and for which this distinction can be made).

bn:00032763n: A story about fairies; told to amuse children
Fairy tales are a type of story which typically features fantasy characters, such as fairies, goblins, elves, trolls, dwarves, giants, mermaids, or gnomes, and usually magic or enchantments. tale

A fairy tale is a type of short story that typically features European folkloric fantasy characters, such as dwarves, elves, fairies, giants, gnomes, goblins, mermaids, trolls, or witches, and usually magic or enchantments.
A folktale featuring fairies or similar fantasy characters.
A fictional story that usually features folkloric characters (such as fairies, goblins, elves, trolls, witches, giants, and talking animals) and enchantments
Fictional story featuring folkloric fantasy characters

bn:00064417n: Princess is the feminine form of prince.
A female member of a royal family other than a queen, especially a daughter or granddaughter.
Royal title. Daughter of a king, queen, or sovereign prince or consort of a prince.
A female member of a royal family other than the queen (especially the daughter of a sovereign)
The daughter of a king, queen, emperor, empress, prince, or princess.

bn:00001530n: A woman is a female human.
An animal of the sex that produces eggs.
An adult human member of the sex that produces ova and bears young.
An adult female person (as opposed to a man)

bn:00068437n: A sail set next above the topgallant on a royal mast
A royal is a small sail flown immediately above the topgallant on square rigged sailing ships.
In large sailing ships, square sail over the topgallant sail.

bn:01669238n: The literary genre generally dealing with themes of magic and fictive medieval technology.
Fantasy refers to constructs of the imagination; in storytelling Fantasy generally refers to a genre that uses magic and other supernatural forms as a primary element of plot, theme, and/or setting.
Fantasy is a genre of fiction that commonly uses magic and other supernatural phenomena as a primary plot element, theme, or setting.
A genre of literature and art that uses magic and other supernatural forms as a primary element of plot and theme. The storyline is often set in a fictional, historically oriented setting.

bn:00024069n: Precious item of headwear, symbolizing the power of a ruler
The Crown (or the reigning monarch) as the symbol of the power and authority of a monarchy
Imperial or regal power, or those who wield it.

A crown is the traditional symbolic form of headgear worn by a monarch or by a deity, for whom the crown traditionally represents power, legitimacy, victory, triumph, honor, and glory, as well as immortality, righteousness, and resurrection.
As worn by a king or queen

bn:00068528n: A person who rules or commands
A person who rules or governs; a person who exercises dominion or controlling power over others.
Potentate is a term for a person with potent, sometimes supreme, power.

bn:00055624n: An autocracy governed by a monarch who usually inherits the authority
A monarchy is a form of government in which sovereignty is actually or nominally embodied in a single individual.
A government with a hereditary head of state (whether as a figurehead or as a powerful ruler).
A government with a hereditary head of state.
A monarchy is a government in which all state authority is formally identified with an individual, or in some cases a ruling couple.
System of government where the state's sovereignty rests in an individual
Form of government with a hereditary head of state.

bn:00034453n: A young female human; (in contrast to boy), a female child or young adult.
A title of respect for a young woman (usually unmarried) with or without a name used.
A young female person, usually a child or teenager.
A girl is any female human from birth through childhood and adolescence to attainment of adulthood when she becomes a woman.
A girl is a female human from birth through childhood and adolescence to attainment of adulthood when she becomes a woman.
